    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA164-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu “poruḷ muṭittu vantāṉ” eṉpatu vāyilkaḷ vāyk (ET: vāyilkaḷāṟ) kēṭṭa tōḻi talaivikku uraittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante, who had head from the mouth of the mediators that he had come after accomplishing wealth, said to HER.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA164">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uṟaituṟan tirunta puṟaviṟ ṟaṉātu</l>
<l>            ceṅkatirc celvaṉ ṟeṟutaliṉ maṇpaka</l>
<l>            vulakumika varunti yayarvuṟu kālaic</l>
<l>            ceṉṟaṉa rāyiṉu naṉṟucey taṉareṉac</l>
<l>            colliṟ ṟeḷippavun teḷital collāy </l>
<l>            ceṅkōl vāḷik koṭuvi lāṭavar</l>
<l>            vampa mākka ḷuyirttiṟam peyartteṉa</l>
<l>            veṅkaṭaṟ ṟaṭaimutaṟ paṭumuṭai taḻīi</l>
<l>            yuṟupacik kuṟunari kuṟukal cellātu</l>
<l>            māṟupuṟak koṭukku matta </l>
<l>            mūṟila rākuta luḷḷā māṟē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>“Even if he has gone</l>
<l rend="indent2">in a time of forgetfulness, the world suffering much,</l>
<l rend="indent">while the earth splits from the scorching of the one who is rich in</l>
<l rend="indent">his(?)<note place="foot">Even if <term xml:lang="ta">taṉātu</term> is just a metrically lengthened form of <term xml:lang="ta">taṉatu</term> (thus T.V.G’s interpretation), what to do with it? In the given position it does not make sense.</note> red beams on the woodland that lay abandoned by rain,</l>
<l rend="indent3">he has done a good thing”,</l>
<l>even when [you] said [so] in order to make it clear<note place="foot">Literally: "even when you made it clear when you said ..."</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent3">you did not say it so as to be clear,<note place="foot">Or, with the variant <term xml:lang="ta">cellāy</term>, taken to be an auxiliary here by T.V.G.: "you didn't gain clarity", and in that case we would have to assume a change of speaker, the one who should understand someone else than the one explaining.</note></l>
<l rend="indent">– because [you?] don't remember that he has no obstacle</l>
<l rend="indent">on the road, where the hungry short jackal,</l>
<l rend="indent2">since the men with bent bows [and] red-stemmed arrows</l>
<l rend="indent2">took away the life essence<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uyir tiṟam</term>: what is <term xml:lang="ta">tiṟam</term> supposed to mean here? It can probably not be meant as a locative suffix, because we need a direct object for <term xml:lang="ta">peyartteṉa</term>.</note> of travelling people,</l>
<l rend="indent">enveloped by the stench coming from the body [covered in] leaves</l>
<l rend="indent">in the hot jungle, doesn’t pass the small stones [and] turns</l>
<l rend="indent3">[its] back on it.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="1b">
    <l>on the woodland that lay abandoned as a residence</l>
</lg>
        </lg>
